Here's the back yard.  It's fully fenced, and the dogs enjoy spending a lot of time out here, daily.  It's also lovely to sit in the south-facing sun.

Lenny is our old man.  His challenges are wind and storms, and loud noises. But, if he can just sit next to you and tremble, he's okay.
He is about 13 years old and was rescued from a city pound. He is sweet, and gentle, and loves his little dog buddies.

Nilla is a terrier mix.  She is the sweetest (and the fattest) of the bunch.  She is SO gentle, and spends much of her awake time washing her buddies. She loves time on a lap, and nothing is better than curling up together on a couch to watch a movie.
She would LOVE to sit on your lap.  She recently tore her ACL, but is recovering nicely, and has the best, happiest attitude ever.

Miles does NOT like to have his picture taken! He runs away. So, this is a rare photo, immediately after which he ran away.... He is a rescue, and I think associates being photographed with all the turmoil of his previous life and traumatic transport.

Here's another rare photo.  He's incredibly smart, and seems to have a second sense about when a camera is pointed his way.  He is also VERY sweet, but shares some issues with Lenny about storms and loud noises.
While our dogs are all rescues, our cats are purebred.  Because three of us are allergic to cats, they had to be hypoallergenic.  Ivan and his sister Katya are Siberian Forest cats.
I don't know if this is just cats, or how they were raised, but these felines definitely know they are royalty.
Ivan and his sister get along very well, though they were born in litters 2 years apart.
Katya has many names, the most descriptive of which are Princess, and "Snitza".
